# Metro/Babel's plugin resolution (used by EAS builds and `eas update`'s local
# export step) walks plain Node directory resolution from deep inside the pnpm
# store and doesn't find pnpm-isolated transitive deps on its own — it needs
# babel-preset-expo's own transitive deps (react-native-worklets,
# @babel/plugin-transform-react-jsx, etc.) reachable at the root. Hoisting
# broadly (like the old node-linker=hoisted did) covers this, but that also
# hoisted a single ambiguous copy of react/@types/react to the root, which deep
# tools (e.g. Next.js's own .d.ts files) picked up via directory-walk instead of
# apps/web's pinned version — apps/web pins React 18, packages/ui and
# apps/mobile pin React 19 for RN compatibility, so a single shared root copy
# breaks one side's typecheck. Hoist everything EXCEPT react/@types/react to
# the root so both concerns are satisfied.
public-hoist-pattern[]=*
public-hoist-pattern[]=!react
public-hoist-pattern[]=!react-dom
public-hoist-pattern[]=!@types/react
public-hoist-pattern[]=!@types/react-dom
hoist-pattern[]=*
hoist-pattern[]=!react
hoist-pattern[]=!react-dom
hoist-pattern[]=!@types/react
hoist-pattern[]=!@types/react-dom
